Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%pack} in a #sieve.

Add the @diced butternut squash{300%g}, @baby carrots{150%g} and chickpeas to a lined #baking tray{}. Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, @paprika{1%sachet}, @Middle Eastern style spice mix{1%sachet} and a good glug of @oil{to taste}. Toss together and spread out in a single layer. Roast until the veg is tender, ~{30-35%minutes}. When 5 mins of cooking time remain, scatter the @almonds{15%g} over the veg then return the tray to the #oven to finish roasting.

Meanwhile, pour 240ml water (double for 4p) into a large #pot. Stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}. Pop a #lid on the pot and remove from the heat. Leave aside for ~{12-15%mins}. Just before serving, stir the @green pesto{1%sachet} through the bulgur, fluffing it up as you go.

> If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Divide your pesto bulgur between #bowls{}. Top with the chickpeas and tender roast veg. Crumble the @Greek style cheese{100%g}(crumbled) over the top. Finish with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.